reviewText: Great DVD! We had it running during our Thanksgiving event. People loved it and great to see the Chevrolet ads!

I gave it a high rating although, on some songs, it looked like the sound man didn't do his job, the voice was a little muffled.  On the whole, it was a pleasant listening experience.  I give it an A-Plus.

This is a nice reminder of what good clean entertainment used to be about. Dinah Shore is a treasure as she sings with her guests. I especially enjoyed seeing Gwen Verdon, as I've always loved Damn Yankees. Dinah definitely had a classy variety show.

Awful Quality. I expected more from a legit disc. I don't like to give bad reviews but I felt I had a responsibility to others who might want to buy this dvd. Save your money unless you are desperate to have this Dinah Shore Show. Pass it by
